# Styling & Design System

## Tamagui Theme System

- Use Tamagui's built-in theme tokens: `$color`, `$space`, `$size`, etc.
- Access theme values via props: `backgroundColor="$background"`
- Use responsive props: `padding={{ xs: '$2', md: '$4' }}`
- Leverage Tamagui's variant system for component states

## Component Styling

```tsx
// Preferred Tamagui styling approach
<YStack
  backgroundColor="$background"
  padding="$4"
  borderRadius="$4"
  gap="$2"
  shadowColor="$shadowColor"
  shadowRadius={4}
>
  <Text color="$color" fontSize="$6">
    Content
  </Text>
</YStack>
```

## Layout Components

- Use `YStack` for vertical layouts
- Use `XStack` for horizontal layouts
- Use `ZStack` for overlapping elements
- Prefer Tamagui layout props over custom CSS

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first approach
- Use Tamagui's responsive props
- Test on multiple screen sizes
- Consider both web and native platforms

## Animation

- Use Moti for animations: `import { MotiView } from 'moti'`
- Prefer Tamagui's built-in animations when available
- Keep animations performant and accessible
- Use spring animations for natural feel

## Dark/Light Mode

- Use Tamagui's theme system for automatic mode switching
- Import theme utilities from `~/interface/theme/`
- Test components in both themes
- Use semantic color tokens, not hardcoded colors

## Accessibility

- Follow Biome's a11y rules (already configured)
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide alt text for images
- Ensure proper color contrast
- Support keyboard navigation

## CSS Guidelines (when needed)

- Minimize custom CSS usage
- Use CSS modules or styled-components if custom CSS needed
- Follow Biome formatting rules (2 spaces, single quotes)
- Prefer Tamagui solutions over custom CSS
